	<div class="grid_8">

		<h1>State News, Inc.</h1>
		
		<img src="http://www.statenews.com/media/00/00/04/21/42143_newsroomp.png" style="padding: 10px 10px 10px 0; float: left;" />
		<p>
			State News, Inc., a privately-held, nonprofit corporation, is the publisher of <em>The State News</em> and <a href="http://statenews.com">StateNews.com</a>, the independent student news organization of <a href="http://msu.edu">Michigan State University</a>. State News, Inc. seeks to produce the finest journalists, designers, advertising professionals, graphic artists and web developers in the nation.
		</p>
		
		<strong>State News Applications and Programming</strong>
		<p>
			In association with <a href="http://detroitsoftworks.com">Detroit Softworks</a>, State News Applications and Programming develops and maintains the <a href="http://detroitsoftworks.com/index.php/page/gryphon">Gryphon Content Management Platform</a>, its associated applications and provides custom application and web development to <em>The State News</em> and its client news organizations.
		</p>
		
		<strong>State News Creative Services</strong>
		<p>
			State News Creative Services provides creative design and campaign management services to a variety of Mid-Michigan businesses. Creative Services gives an advertiser the ability to project a focused and concise campaign across multiple media.
		</p>
		
		<strong>State News Board of Directors</strong>
		<p>
			The business, property and affairs, of State News, Inc., is managed by a board of 12 Directors. Of the members of the Board, three are employed full-time in news media or with recent full-time experience in news media, and, if possible, alumni of Michigan State University; three are tenure stream faculty, faculty emeriti, and professional staff with job security as defined by the university; and six are students registered at Michigan State University.
		</p>
		
		<p>
			Any person seeking consideration for a directorship may submit a resume to the Board of Directors in advance of the annual meeting. Notice of application deadline is published in <em>The State News</em> and on <a href="http://statenews.com/work">StateNews.com/work</a>. Each Director holds office for a term of two years and until a successor can be elected and qualified or until his/her resignation or removal. No member of the Board or operating staff, student or professional, may serve both positions simultaneously. Moreover, no Board member may seek a position on the operating staff without first resigning from the board.
		</p>
		
